snippet.textDisplay:
1st story: Turns out devices made purely to listen in and collect data do in fact listen in and collect data. 
Frankly the fact they managed to get people to pay for these things is hilarious. What they and others basically did was sell you a microphone that does't actually do anything other than the voice assistant on your smartphone that you never use, so you put it in your home and for a couple of weeks you have fun with the novelty feeling like the jetsons and then ... it sits there, by your TV or on a side table or wherever ... listening, listening, listening until you change the wifi password and remember it's there. 

At least governements put bugs in your house for free
